<subSubSection id="18A76570782F8A45A09179F87701D480" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" type="description">
<paragraph id="500236FB782F8A45A09179F87701D480" blockId="1.[151,1437,1679,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="62C9EAE9782F8A45A09179F87365D5F0" bold="true" box="[199,337,1751,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">Description</emphasis>
. See 
<bibRefCitation id="342C4B0A782F8A45A1C079F87000D5F0" author="Walter" box="[406,564,1751,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Walter, C. (1911) Hydracarina der Aru-Inseln. In: Merton, H. (Ed.), Ergebnisse einer zoolog. Forschungsreise in den sudostlichen Molukken, 2, pp. 207 - 222." type="journal article" year="1911">Walter (1911)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="342C4B0A782F8A45A22479F87130D5F0" author="Viets" box="[626,772,1751,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda- Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement, 13, 484 - 594, 595 - 738." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets (1935)</bibRefCitation>
. Additional characters: Male idiosoma 834 long and 753 wide, female idiosoma 899 long and 826 wide. Genital field: male 259 long, and 316 wide, female 267 long and 332 wide. The male has an oblique anterior margin of the genital valve, in the female this margin is straight with a short medial extension. The pre-genital sclerite of the male is rhomboid in the male and triangular in the female. The configuration of the mediodorsal plates dg5 and dg6 (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="342C4B0A782F8A45A311784771E7D480" author="Harvey" box="[839,979,1896,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Harvey, M. S. (1988) New species of the water mite family Hydryphantidae (Acarina) from the Northern Territory, Australia. The Beagle, Records of the Northern Territory of Arts and Sciences, 5, 17 - 26." type="journal article" year="1988">Harvey1988</bibRefCitation>
) of both sexes is asymmetrical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="18A76570782F8A46A09178A37711D3F8" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="500236FB782F8A46A09178A37711D3F8" blockId="1.[151,1437,1679,2029]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis id="62C9EAE9782F8A45A09178A37300D4A5" bold="true" box="[199,308,1932,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="342C4B0A782F8A45A11478A3703CD4A4" author="Jin" box="[322,520,1932,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Jin, D. &amp; Guo, Z. (1993) [A new species of Mamersinae, a first record subfamily of water mites from China (Acari: Hydryphantidae.] Journal of Guizhou Agricultural College, Supplement 12, 61 - 63. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="1993">Jin &amp; Guo (1993)</bibRefCitation>
stated that, in describing 
<taxonomicName id="97BD4D78782F8A45A37E78A276B6D4A4" authority="Jin &amp; Guo, 1993" authorityName="Jin &amp; Guo" authorityYear="1993" box="[808,1154,1932,1957]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paddicola">
<emphasis id="62C9EAE9782F8A45A37E78A27189D4A4" box="[808,957,1932,1956]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">M. paddicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="342C4B0A782F8A45A39278A376B6D4A4" author="Jin" box="[964,1154,1932,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Jin, D. &amp; Guo, Z. (1993) [A new species of Mamersinae, a first record subfamily of water mites from China (Acari: Hydryphantidae.] Journal of Guizhou Agricultural College, Supplement 12, 61 - 63. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="1993">Jin &amp; Guo, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species differed in the presence of two pairs of posterolateral plates. However, they overlooked 
<taxonomicName id="97BD4D78782F8A45A478789E76A4D4C8" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1911" box="[1070,1168,1969,1992]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rouxi">
<emphasis id="62C9EAE9782F8A45A478789E76A4D4C8" box="[1070,1168,1969,1992]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">M. rouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species they did not mention in the paper. Their illustrations match the description of the latter species, and we therefore propose to synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="97BD4D78782C8A46A17E7FB673F4D3B0" authorityName="Jin &amp; Guo" authorityYear="1993" box="[296,448,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paddicola">
<emphasis id="62C9EAE9782C8A46A17E7FB673F4D3B0" box="[296,448,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">M. paddicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="97BD4D78782C8A46A2537FB67053D3AF" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1911" box="[517,615,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rouxi">
<emphasis id="62C9EAE9782C8A46A2537FB67053D3AF" box="[517,615,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">M. rouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The differences in the shape of the pre-genital sclerite and the genital valves was not mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="342C4B0A782C8A46A1B07F937041D3D5" author="Viets" box="[486,629,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda- Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement, 13, 484 - 594, 595 - 738." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets (1935)</bibRefCitation>
. The species is new for the fauna of 
<collectingCountry id="28AA766B782C8A46A4447F93764DD3D5" box="[1042,1145,188,213]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. It has been found on the Aru Islands, 
<collectingRegion id="9279F819782C8A46A1717FCF73B0D3F8" box="[295,388,224,248]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="9279F819782C8A46A1EC7FF0702BD3F8" box="[442,543,223,248]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="28AA766B782C8A46A2787FF070ABD3F8" box="[558,671,223,248]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, Wiles pers. comm.), 
<collectingCountry id="28AA766B782C8A46A3C57FF071E2D3F8" box="[915,982,223,248]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="28AA766B782C8A46A45A7FF07644D3F8" box="[1036,1136,223,248]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
